<TITLE> 2 get death, 7 get life for Rusho murder </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 30 (bdnews24.com)  A Dhaka court on Sunday sentenced two people to death and seven others to life imprisonment in the Arifur Rahman Rusho murder case. Judge Md Nurul Huda of Speedy Trial Tribunal-3 handed down death sentences to Kazi Abdullh Al Mamun alias Babu and Siddiqur Rahman Siddique. The life convicts are Raju Miah alias Dukhu, Jamal Khan, Mohammad Ali, Saiful Islam Shaheed, Liton Miah, Abul Hossain Dipu and Jakir Sarder. The victim's father Dr Shafiqul Alam expressed satisfaction over the verdict. Rusho, the son of Lt Col Alam and Dr Amburi Begum, was killed by muggers on May 24 last year in front of the National Credit and Commerce Bank on Satmasjid Road in Dhanmondi while he was returning home after withdrawing cash from the bank Joynul Abedin, father of Rusho's girlfriend, Shakrun was also with him. As they were getting into their car, the muggers attempted to snatch the money, shooting at Rusho's head before fleeing the scene. He was rushed to Bangladesh Medical College Hospital where he died later the same day. The murder case was filed with Dhanmondi Police Station. bdnews24
